Package com.rafaelbattesti.jungle

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DenTile
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a DenTile.
    If your opponent occupies your Den, you are finished!
    A DenTile do not allow a Piece of the same side to enter it.
    GameExtended
    This Class intends to define the methods to initialize a Jungle game.
    It contains a Main method that instantiates the GameExtended itself and passes it to a GameView instance.
    JumpingPiece
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a JumpingPiece.
    A JumpingPiece can jump across WaterTile as long as there is no SwimmingPiece in front of it.
    It can take any Piece on the other side of WaterTile, including the Rat, if it is out of the Water.
    StrongestPiece
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a StrongestPiece.
    A StrongestPiece can take any opponent's Piece but the Rat.
    SwimmingPiece
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a Swimming piece.
    A SwimmingPiece cannot take any opponent's Piece when leaving the WaterTile.
    A SwimmingPiece can take another SwimmingPiece while both are on WaterTile.
    Please refer to subclass WeakestPiece for details about the Rat taking the Elephant.
    TrapTile
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a TrapTile.
    If one of your pieces is on a trap, take care, anyone can take it!
    Likewise, if your opponent's have a piece on a trap, it is the perfect opportunity to take it using a lower rank piece!
    WaterTile
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a WaterTile.
    The WaterTile allows a SwimmingPiece to enter.
    The WaterTile also allows a JumpingPiece to jump over it, as long as there are no SwimmingPiece on it.
    WeakestPiece
    This Class intends to define the methods to instantiate a WeakestPiece.
    A WeakestPiece can take an opponent's WeakestPiece and StrongestPiece, if not leaving the Water
    (validated by super.canTakePiece(Piece pieceToBeTaken).
